e criteria are unaffordable</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt"> for young single people</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">. This significantly reduces the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">number of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">available properties with few affordable alternatives. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">There are some local authorities pursuing innovative policies to try </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">increase available accommodation. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">Westminster</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">’s Fair Share Housing Scheme</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">is providing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">good quality shared accommodation, affordable on the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt"> living wage, to those making a contri</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">bution to the local economy</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt"> These properties will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">be around a third cheaper than an equivalent arrangement in the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5pt">PRS</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10.5